2.2 What is LIDAR?\par
\b0 LiDAR, an acronym for \ldblquote light detection and ranging,\rdblquote  is a remote-sensing technology that uses laser beams to measure precise distances and movement in an environment, in real time [6]. LiDAR data can be used to generate everything from detailed topographic maps to the precise, dynamic 3D models that are required to safely guide an autonomous vehicle through a rapidly and constantly changing environment. LiDAR technology is also used to assess hazards and natural disasters such as lava flows, landslides, tsunamis and floods.\b\par
