\fs24 2.6 Material Selection for Structures\fs22\par
\b0 One of the most important steps in ensuring the system's strength and flexibility is the mounting structure's material selection. In this project, the physical characteristics required to sustain the sensors and UGV components as well as the design standards drove the material selection. With the help of the manufacturer, it was possible to obtain the 3D CAD models for the AgileX Ranger 4WS 4WD UGV and the LIDAR sensors, which included important specifications and precise measurements. With the help of the manufacturer, it was feasible to precisely measure the sensors' size and location of mounting points, guaranteeing that they would work with the current design.\par
Because of their exceptional strength-to-weight ratio, resistance to corrosion, and ease of modification, aluminum 30x30 T-slot rails were chosen as the material for the mounting structure. Because of its ease of adjustment, this material was especially well-suited for enabling adaptable sensor setups according to mission requirements. The aluminum rails also provided a sturdy foundation for mounting the sensors securely while reducing extra weight, which is essential for preserving the UGV's performance and agility.\par
