\b 3.3 Prototype Development and Material Selection\b0\par
To further evaluate the design, we moved on to prototyping. One of the challenges encountered during the design phase was the need for a material that could withstand the environmental conditions typically faced by UGVs. To address this, we used high-temperature-resistant material to 3D print a prototype of the mounting frame for one of the sensors. This allowed for a more tangible evaluation of the mounting design, including assessing the fit, durability, and flexibility of the structure in real-world conditions. The 3D printed prototype provided valuable insights into the mounting structure\rquote s practical viability and allowed for adjustments before proceeding to full-scale fabrication.\par

